Date: Wed 30 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Kyodo News via Japan today, 30 Mar 2005 [edited]
<http://www.japantoday.com/e/?content=news&cat=7&id=332364>

North Korea may have culled 10 million chickens over bird flu
-----------------------------------------------
North Korea may have culled as many as 10 million chickens in the Pyongyang
area alone, following the recent outbreak of bird flu in the country, the
South Korean daily Donga Ilbo reported on Wednesday [30 Mar 2005].
Citing informed sources who met with recent visitors to North Korea, the
report said North Korea is said to have culled all chickens bred in the
Pyongyang area to prevent the spread of the disease.
