[3]
Date: 30 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Donga (North Korean
<http://english.donga.com/srv/service.php3?biid=2005033189148>
North Korea Fights against the Bird Flu
-------------------
On Tuesday [29 Mar 2005], the North Korean Central News Agency disclosed
images of epidemic control officials sterilizing the chicken factory where
the bird flu outbreak was reported. On the same day, the South Korean
government handed over a notification over to the North through Panmunjeom,
asking for information concerning the bird flu outbreak and also expressing
its intention to help in any way possible.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The discrepancy between data cited in different newswires dealing with the
North Korea AI situation illuminates the need for an official report.
Published data, such as culling figures, remain ambiguous. For comparison:
during the H5N1 epizootic in South Korea, December 2003 - March 2004, 19
outbreaks were recorded; the total number of affected and culled birds
(chickens and ducks) officially (and timely) reported was 399 898. - Mod.AS]
